# Ignore-rect mask for probability_smoke (NumOS SDL2 emulator visual test).
#
# Reason: the ONLY volatile region on the ProbabilityApp screen across separate
# launches is the StatusBar clock. The app opens with default parameters mu=0,
# sigma=1, x=0 and draws a static bell curve (lv_chart) + PDF/CDF readout; it has no
# blinking input cursor and no animation once its 200 ms fade-in settles, so the body
# (parameter panel, results, bell curve) is byte-stable. The clock label is drawn by
# StatusBar::updateClock() from the real wall clock (time() -> localtime ->
# "%02d:%02d", src/ui/StatusBar.cpp), so HH:MM reflects the minute each scripted run
# happens to execute on. Two launches in different minutes (or hours) therefore
# differ only inside the clock glyphs. This is expected per-minute UI
# nondeterminism, NOT a renderer bug — the renderer is frozen, so it is masked in the
# comparator instead of edited in src/.
#
# Region: the SAME shared StatusBar clock as settings_smoke / math_showcase_smoke.
# The label is aligned LV_ALIGN_LEFT_MID,6 in lv_font_montserrat_12
# (StatusBar.cpp:61-65) and is always exactly 5 glyphs ("HH:MM"), so its box spans
# ~x[6..38] y[8..16]. Because both the HOUR and the MINUTE digits can vary across
# arbitrary launches, the mask covers the WHOLE label, not just the minutes.
#
# Rect = full HH:MM label box (~x[6..38] y[8..16]) padded ~2px on each side ->
# x[4..40] y[6..18]. This is tight to the clock: the app title is centered (x~160),
# the battery/angle/modifier are right-aligned (x>240), and the Probability body
# (parameters + bell curve) renders below the y=24 StatusBar separator — none are
# masked.
#
# x,y,w,h
4,6,37,13
